track_notes: Route over Tryfan, before Glyder Fach and Glyder Fawr.  Descent via Devils Kitchen and Llyn Idwal

A linear route. Car parked at barred gate to tarmac quarry road up to Marchlyn Mawr Reservoir. Foel Goch and Glyder Fach bagged en route (NOT SOTA). Scree slope from SH6596 5846 reccied, but decided against using so instead took the safer longer route to Tryfan via the Miners Track. CAUTIONARY NOTE do not take the route up Tryfan against the wall. It was a risky scramble with too much exposure. Suggest you walk on 100m west beyond the ladder stile at the wall and then go up right the way I came down. It will be much safer then. This was a fantastic challenging walk which gains you 34 points outside the winter season. From Idwal Cottage YHA I got a taxi using A1 Taxis (Bethesda) to retrieve my car, returnign to the YHA at Idwal Cottage where I spent the night. next day climbed NW-002 and NW-013 - see my other track for this walk. Started walk at 10.40am and finished at 19.05pm 24-07-2017.
